Karl Hammar
owl:Ontology.dc:description: This ontology imports all RealEstateCore (REC) modules and thus gives the fullest expressivity that REC allows. You can use this ontology as-is, or you can construct your own ontology by importing individual REC modules.
owl:Ontology.dc:title: RealEstateCore Full
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment:
Version 3.0-beta1 is a major refactoring of REC:
* Properties have been defined as being single-domain and single-range * Meronomy properties have been refactored to allow transitive traversal of the parthood hierarchy from RealEstate all the way down to individual devices using the isPartOf and hasPart superproperties ** This has required refactoring of the relations Building <-> BuildingComponent and Device <-> DeviceComponent (the latter is removed) * Class naming has been simplified * Module boundaries have been clarified and three modules (lease, metadata, agents) have been added

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The agent leasing some leasable object.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Leased by

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: actuationCommand is the event of the system [e.g. a digital twin] responsible for sending the actuation to the actuator
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: actuationCommand

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: actuationRequest is the incoming request to perform an actuation [to the digital twin]
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: actuationRequest

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: actuationResponse is the value returned from an actuation as a reponse
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: actuationResponse

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The time stamp for the event of the underlying system intiating the actuation command.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasActuationCommandTime

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The time stamp for when a request for an actuation arrived.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasActuationRequestTime

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The time stamp for a possible response from actuation process.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasActuationResponseTime

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Time when an object or result was processed in a system.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasProcessedTime

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A LaboratoryDry is a laboratory where computational or applied mathematical analyses are done on a computer-generated model to simulate a phenomenon in the physical realm.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: LaboratoryDry

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A LaboratoryWet is a type of laboratory where it is necessary to handle various types of chemicals and potential "wet" hazards, so the room has to be carefully designed, constructed, and controlled to avoid spillage and contamination.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: LaboratoryWet

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Room for making audio and/or video recordings. A.ka. studio.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RecordingRoom

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Room for staff to take breaks.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: StaffRoom

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The level of storey, a.k.a. floorplan
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Storey level

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: For e.g. medical or other treatment or consultation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TreatmentRoom

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A non-physical Building. Belongs to a RealEstate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Virtual building

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A non-physical component. Belongs to a Building . One Building may have zero, one, or many Virtual components. E.g a temperature value from an external service for the area of a building.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Virtual building component

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The act of changing the state of something.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actuation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A description of what kind of input the Actuator accepts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actuation interface

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An actuator is a component that is responsible for moving and controlling a mechanism or system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actuator

owl:Class.rdfs:label: BACnetConfiguration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Type of communiaction bus for the Device.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DeviceCommunication

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The main function or purpose of a Device.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Device function type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Failed attempt or unexpected result when tried to do something (e.g. read a Sensor).

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Observation of a phenomena. Made by a Sensor. Used with hasValue.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Observation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Description of the context or media that a sensor or actuator is operating within.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Placement context

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The power source for the device.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Thing which detects or measures a physical property and records, indicates, or otherwise responds to it.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Things that can be leased (e.g., buildings, rooms, equipment, etc.).
